<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Snaggletooth:
[B]"Anyone who feels like making your play experience worse as part of their effort to pretend they have self-esteem can do so just as easily on PVP, and they do."

That's exactly the assumption that I am telling you is wrong.  In the above quote, replace the word "your" with "my", and I think you have it right. 

It may be true that some schmuck can grief YOU into submission - but not ME.  You are telling me that people are making my play experience less enjoyable, when in fact, I welcome PvP.  That's why I play on the Zeks!

And the fungi monk example is a great one, because it demonstrates the difference between those with skill, and those without.  You believe fungi monk to be unstoppable, whereas I view him as a predator cutting down my competition for mobs.  He can't kill me, and I can't kill him.  He looks for an easier target - like you!

That's why people leave with a bad impression - because you don't know how to PvP.  These types try out the server, get PKd, whine over /ooc, then quit the server.  Those players are typically referred to as "bluebies."  They can't PvP their way out of a wet paper sack, which is totally understandable.  We all sucked at it at one time.  NEVER did I whine about it.  EVER.

You called me a griefer.  I am not that at all, and nothing I have said mentions anything dishonorable about my actions on the field of combat.  For you to assume that I am a griefer, makes me believe that you have nothing but utter contempt for those who choose the path of combat.

Anyone with PvP skills and speaks openly about those skills, and is proud of those skills, is a grief player in your mind.  If you are arrogant about you PvP prowess, you MUST be a griefer.

Like you, I also don't think it matters who is better at this video game.  But, let's be honest here, PvP is a skill that most blue server players lack.  And for that reason only, in general, they are not as good at EQ as the general population of the Zeks.

I haven't heard a logical argument yet as to why this is untrue.

Use me as an example...

You don't have to like me.  You don't have to agree with me.  But if you can't explain to me why you are as good or better at EQ than me, then I obviously will continue to believe that I am a much more well rounded EQ player, and therefore better at EQ, than you are.  This is assuming that you don't have well honed PvP skills, and that we are equal in terms of PvE skill.

It's very basic logic, and objective thinking.  Eliminate your emotions concerning the issue at hand, and view it as an outsider would.  I think you'll agree with my assessment.

I know I have the PvP superiority complex.  I could care less what anyone thinks about that.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
